1. Installation Guide

This is a quick guide on installation, and updating.

1.1 Plugin Installation

To install WooCommerce Product plugin you must have a working and latest version of WordPress and WooCommerce plugin already installed. For information on installing the WordPress , please see the WordPress Codex - Installing WordPress. For installing the WooCommerce and configure the shop please visit the following link WooThemes - Installing WooCommerce.

Now the next step is the Extendons WooCommerce Registration Plugin installation. In the full .ZIP archive you have downloaded from Codecanyon.net you will find a file called extendon_registration_fields.zip. This file is the installable .ZIP archive you can install via WordPress.

Now is time to install Extendons WooCommerce Registration Fields, please read these steps carefully.

 

Installing from WordPress

Follow the steps bellow to install from WordPress Admin Dashboard

  • Navigate to Plugins
  • Click Install Plugins and click Add New
  • Click the Upload Plugin button
  • Navigate extendon_registration_fields.zip on your computer and click Install Now
  • When installation is done please click Activate to activate plugin

 

Installing using FTP

Follow the steps bellow to install using FTP

  • Unzip extendon_registration_fields.zip to a desired location on your computer. These extracted files will be uploaded later via FTP
  • Connect to your server via FTP (Use FileZilla or any other FTP client)
  • Navigate to /wp-content/plugins/ server directory
  • Locate the local directory where you have unzipped the extendon_registration_fields.zip archive
  • Upload local folder /extendon_registration_fields/ to remote /wp-content/plugins/

To activate the newly installed plugin navigate to Plugins and click the Activate button within the Extendons WooCommerce Registration Plugin.

1.2 Plugin Updates

Update from WordPress Admin

Follow the steps bellow to update from WordPress Admin Dashboard

  • Navigate to Plugins
  • Find the currently installed Extendons WooCommerce Registration Plugin and click Deactivate
  • After deactivation click Delete to remove the old version (your saved setting will not be lost)
  • Click Install Plugins and click Add New
  • Click the Upload Plugin button
  • Navigate the new version archive extendon_registration_fields.zip on your computer and click Install Now
  • When installation is done please click Activate to activate plugin

 

Update using FTP

Follow the steps bellow to update using FTP

  • Unzip the new version archive extendon_registration_fields.zip to a desired location on your computer. These extracted files will be uploaded later via FTP
  • Connect to your server via FTP (Use FileZilla or any other FTP client)
  • Navigate to /wp-content/plugins/ server directory and delete the current plugin folder /extendon_registration_fields/
  • Locate the local directory where you have unzipped the new version archive extendon_registration_fields.zip
  • Upload local folder /extendon_registration_fields/ to remote /wp-content/plugins/

1.3 Set Registration Fields

After installation of the module navigate to

  •  Registration Fields → Registration Fields

 

Text Fields

  • Drag Text field from Form Fields and Drop in Registration Form Fields
  • Set Label of field
  • Check required checkbox if you want to make field Required.
  • Set place holder for field
  • Set field width Half or Full
  • Set field message if any
  • Implement conditional logic if any.

 

Textarea Fields

  • Drag Textarea field from Form Fields and Drop in Registration Form Fields
  • Set Label of field
  • Check required checkbox if you want to make field Required.
  • Set place holder for field
  • Set field width Half or Full

Social Login (Facebook)

  • Navigate to Registration Fields → Settings
  • Click on Facebook Settings Tab
  • Enable Login with facebook
  • Enter Facebook App ID.
  • Enter Facebook App Secret.
  • You can get these from https://developers.facebook.com/

 

Social Login (Twitter)

  • Navigate to Registration Fields → Settings
  • Click on Twitter Settings Tab
  • Enable Login with twitter
  • Enter Twitter App Consumer Key.
  • Enter Twitter App Consumer Secret.
  • Enter Twitter App Access Tocken
  • Enter Twitter App Access Tocken Secret
  • You can get these from  http://dev.twitter.com/

 

Admin can see user entered field’s data in

Users → Edit User

 

Fields are also sent in admin email.

 

On Front end Registration form fields are shown on the registration form.

Social login button are shown after login form.

User can also check his/her fields in My Account.

2. User Guide

After installation of plugin, login to admin panel and flush your cache storage.

2.1 How to Add/Edit Registration Fields

Step 1 – Backend:

To add new registration fields, go to "Registration Fields” at the backend. Here you will find the list of all the fields. Click on field on the left and drag it to the fight. You can customize the field according to your requirements. For the purpose of this demo we have added the following information.

 

Step 2 – Frontend:

Now at the frontend you will find the added fields in the registration form highlighted. You can also go back and edit this field.

 

 

2.2 How to Configure the Plugin

At the backend, go to "Registration Fields". Here you will find the following settings:

General Settings:

  1. Account Section Title: Main heading of the account section
  2. Profile Section Title: Main heading of the profile section.

 

Facebook Settings:

  1. Login With Facebook: Enable or Disable login with facebook feature on registration page.
  2. Facebook App ID: This is the facebook app id, you can get this id from your facebook app settings.
  3. Facebook App Secret: This is the facebook app secret, you can get this id from your facebook app settings.

 

 

 

Twitter Settings:

  1. Login With Twitter: Enable or Disable login with twitter feature on registration page.
  2. Twitter App Consumer Key: This is the twitter app consumer key, you can get this key from your twitter app keys and access token tab.
  3. Twitter App Consumer Secret: This is the twitter app consumer secret, you can get this key from your twitter app keys and access token tab.
  4. Twitter App Access Token: This is the twitter app access token, you can get this key from your twitter app keys and access token tab.
  5. Twitter App Access Token Secret: This is the twitter app access token secret, you can get this key from your twitter app keys and access token tab.
